## Context

The multilayer-detection paper (QSS target) needs a focused technical
supplement assembled from the existing pool (`technical-report.qmd`
includes). The supplement covers only the 6 methods used in the paper;
the full 18-method zoo stays in `technical-report.qmd`.

Pool architecture: `technical-report.qmd` is composed of modular
`_includes/` fragments. The supplement assembles a subset of those
fragments — no prose duplication.

## Actions

1. Create `content/multilayer-detection-techrep.qmd` with the following
   include sequence:
   - `_includes/techrep/overview.md` (framing)
   - `_includes/techrep/zscore.md` (Z-score standardisation)
   - `_includes/techrep/null-model.md` (permutation null model)
   - `_includes/zoo/S2_energy.md` (primary semantic detector)
   - `_includes/zoo/L1_js.md` (primary lexical detector)
   - `_includes/zoo/G9_community.md` (primary citation detector)
   - `_includes/zoo/C2ST_embedding.md` (robustness check — embedding)
   - `_includes/zoo/C2ST_lexical.md` (robustness check — lexical)
   - Plus any other methods cited in the paper's §4/§5 (audit
     `multilayer-detection.qmd` for method references before finalising
     the list).

2. Add YAML front matter mirroring `technical-report.qmd` style
   (title, author, date, metadata-files, bibliography, pdf-engine).

3. Create `MULTILAYER_TECHREP_INCLUDES` variable in `multilayer-detection.mk`
   listing the included fragments as Make prerequisites.

4. Add `output/content/multilayer-detection-techrep.pdf` target to
   `multilayer-detection.mk`, depending on
   `content/multilayer-detection-techrep.qmd $(MULTILAYER_TECHREP_INCLUDES)
   $(BIB) content/technical-report-vars.yml`.

5. Add the target to the `papers:` phony in `Makefile`.

## Test

`grep -c 'include _includes' content/multilayer-detection-techrep.qmd`
returns ≥ 6. `make output/content/multilayer-detection-techrep.pdf`
succeeds (or degrades gracefully when figure PNGs are absent).

## Dependencies

- PR #737 (t0095-rename-companion-paper) must be merged first.
